The White House has announced new regulations that further implement President Obama's policy of normalizing relations with Cuba. The Departments of the Treasury and Commerce have taken steps to revise existing Cuba sanctions, with the goal of empowering the Cuban people and promoting a more prosperous Cuba that respects human rights. The regulatory changes include enhancements to telecommunications and internet-based services in Cuba. The United States remains committed to engaging with Cuba and improving the lives of ordinary Cubans. The White House Press Secretary also addressed other topics, such as Donald Trump's recent controversial comments and the situation in Syria.